Etymology 1[edit]

Pronunciation[edit]

  • (Classical) IPA(key): /ˈad.le.woː/, [ˈad̪.lɛ.woː]
  • (Ecclesiastical) IPA(key): /ˈad.le.vo/, [ˈad̪.lɛ.vɔ]

Verb[edit]

adlevō (present infinitive adlevāre, perfect active adlevāvī, supine adlevātum); first conjugation

  1. Alternative form of allevō

Etymology 2[edit]

Pronunciation[edit]

  • (Classical) IPA(key): /adˈleː.woː/, [ad̪ˈleː.woː]
  • (Ecclesiastical) IPA(key): /adˈle.vo/, [ad̪ˈlɛː.vɔ]

Verb[edit]

adlēvō (present infinitive adlēvāre, perfect active adlēvāvī, supine adlēvātum); first conjugation

  1. Alternative form of allēvō
